\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Scarcely invest in children education, are poorly fed and suffer from health
 problems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Are worried and anxioust, so that their sleep and work are interefered.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Fail to make trivial investments (
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

micro-finance
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 help - useless).
 they cannot avoid cutting on their meals when income declines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Yet, they spend a significant portion of their income on: alcohol, cigarettes,
 festivals, etc.
 Spending this money on educatino would transofrm the prospects of their
 children.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such typical family does not pay rent on time and doesn't send their children
 to school, yet they spend money on cellphones and drinking.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In India and Africa househoulds spend enormous emount of money on festivals
 and funerals (respectively).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Possible explanations to this phenomena might include:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Conspicuous consumption
\series default
 
\series bold
(Moav-Neeman)
\series default
: people, even the poorest ones, want to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

show off
